	git push origin master 					//publish master 



For Changing Branch :

	git branch -a							//list out all the branches, including remote branch
	git branch -r							//list out all the remote branch
	git checkout develop 					//switch to develop
	git checkout master  					//switch to master
	

Updating Git Branches and try to pull remote branch to local:

	git fetch origin						//Fetch the branches from the remote repository
	git branch -a							//list out all the branches, including remote branch , red ones are remote
	
	git checkout -b <local-branch-name> origin/<remote-branch-name>  //Create a local branch that track the remote branch
	



Commit Format:

	<Name of added feature> 
	<Explaination of the feature> <Simple Explaination of the added algorithm> <Purpose of adding the feature>
	
		<Separate with ENTER>
	
	<Name of second added feature>........
	
		<Separate with ENTER>
	
	<Name of third added feature>.........
	
		<Separate with ENTER>
	
	<Add Signed-off-by>